<item>
            <title>[JOHNZON-333] Invalid String serialization from JsonB string objects</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/JOHNZON-333</link>
                <project id="12315523" key="JOHNZON">Johnzon</project>
                    <description>&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
jsonb.toJson(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;test&quot;&lt;/span&gt;);
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;should result in &quot;test&quot; as String. That includes quote.&lt;br/&gt;
 The spec says&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;3.3.1 java.lang.String, Character&lt;br/&gt;
 Instances of type java.lang.String and java.lang.Character are serialized to JSON String values as defined within RFC 7159 Section 7 (Strings) &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;1&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; in UTF-8 encoding without a byte order mark.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
