                            <comment id="17271629" author="romain.manni-bucau" created="Mon, 25 Jan 2021 19:39:46 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Json strings are quoted values so sounds expected no? At least was in tck at some point IIRC.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17271637" author="struberg" created="Mon, 25 Jan 2021 19:53:49 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;but we return test as java String so &lt;tt&gt;&quot;test&quot;&lt;/tt&gt; and not &lt;tt&gt;&quot;\&quot;test\&quot;&quot;&lt;/tt&gt; in Java as we should.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17271645" author="romain.manni-bucau" created="Mon, 25 Jan 2021 20:05:20 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Ok, got abused by the quotes. Yes must be quoted. We have a toggle for it but should be the default in jsonb module. Wonder if we have 2 codepath for it.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
